Package com.avaya.ic.sdk

Interface Summary
AddressBook The AddressBook interface provides capabilities to retrieve informtion about addressable agents and queues that have been administered in IC.
AddressBookAgentEntry Represents a single agent entry in the AddressBook.
AddressBookAgentQuery Represents a query that can be used to search for appropriates agents in the users AddressBook
AddressBookEntry Represents a single entry in the AddressBook.
AddressBookQueueEntry Represents a single queue entry in the AddressBook.
AddressBookQueueQuery Represents a query that can be used to search for appropriates queues in the users AddressBook
Application The Application interface is the primary interface or starting point for any custom application that uses the IC Client SDK.
Attachment Represents an email attachment.
AttachmentList Represents a collection of Attachments.
CallOption Represents the optional parameters that can be passed by an SDK client when a call is placed.
CallOptions Represents the optional parameters that an SDK client can pass when a call is placed.
CategoryCode Represents a Category code.
CategoryCodesList Represents a collection of CategoryCodes.
CategoryGroup Represents a Category Group.
CategoryGroupList Represents a collection of CategoryGroups.
Channel The Channel interface is a generic representation of a delivery channel in IC.
ChannelList Represents a collection of Channels.
ChatChannel Represents a Channel that can deliver chat media interactions.
ChatMediaInteraction Represents a chat interaction.
ChatMediaInteractionRecord Represents a record of a historical chat interaction that a customer had with the contact center.
Code Represents a Code entity with various properties.
CodesList Represents a list of codes.
CustomerHistory A history of the interaction between a specific customer and IC.
CustomerHistoryRecord Represents a single historical contact that the customer has had with the contact center.
Document Represents a document delivered to the agent through a delivery channel.
DocumentList Contains a list of Documents.
DocumentRecord Represents a historical contact made by the customer with the contact center using a non-interactive media such as email.
DraftDocument A generic representation of an outbound document.
DraftList Represents a collection of Drafts.
EmailChannel Represents a channel that can deliver EmailDocuments.
EmailDocument Represents any email.
EmailDraft Used to send an outbound email.
EmailMessage Represents an email message, and provides access to the basic fields of the email.
EmailMessageRecord Represents a record of an email message exchange between a customer and a user in the contact center.
ICPropertyStore Represents a store for all IC properties that are sent from the server to the client.
LoginOption Represents the optional parameters that can be passed by an SDK client when a user logs in to IC.
LoginOptions Represents the optional parameters that an SDK client can pass when a user logs in to IC.
MediaInteraction Represents an interaction between two or more parties occurring in real time over media.
MediaInteractionList Contains a list of MediaInteractions.
MediaInteractionRecord Represents a historical contact made by the customer with the contact center using an interactive media such as voice or chat.
NameValue Represents a name-value list entry, or name-value pair.
NameValueList Represents a list of name-value pairs, or entries.
OutcomeCode The outcome code selected by the user as wrapup data for assigned work.
ParticipantList Represents a list of participants working on the Interaction.
Party Represents an entity or participant involved in a MediaInteraction.
ReasonCode The reason code selected by the user as wrapup data for assigned work.
RecordsList Represents a collection of Records.
SDKAppContext Represents the context to be used to connect to the SDK Server bridge.
Session A Session is created when an agent logs in successfully to IC.
TranscriptDocument Represents a chat transcript document.
TranscriptLine Represents a message sent into the chat room, and reflects the displayable elements of a chat transcript.
TranscriptLineList Represents a collection of TranscriptLines.
User Represents the User associated with the Session.
VoiceChannel Represents the Voice media channel.
VoiceMediaInteraction Represents a voice call.
VoiceMediaInteractionRecord Represents a record of a historical voice interaction that a customer had with the contact center.
WorkItem The WorkItem represents an unit of work that is assigned to an IC user.
WorkItemHistory A history of how a specific WorkItem traversed through the IC system.
WorkList The WorkList is a collection of items assigned to an IC user.
WrapupRecord Represents a record of the Wrapup options that the contact center user selected during wrap up for the historical contact.
WrapupSelection Represents a single WrapupSelection.
WrapupSelectionList Represents a collection of WrapupSelections.
